---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
        <title>Privacy — hyprwhspr</title>
        <meta
            name="description"
            content="hyprwhspr is free, open source, and built by a solo developer with no corporate incentives. When using local models, nothing leaves your machine."
        />
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
        <link
            href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap"
            rel="stylesheet"
        />
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="page">
            <header class="header">
                <a href="/" class="back">← hyprwhspr</a>
            </header>

            <main>
                <div class="title-block">
                    <span class="page-tag">privacy</span>
                    <h1>Zero shenanigans.</h1>
                    <p class="lede">
                        hyprwhspr is built on a simple premise: a tool that
                        listens to you should never report back about you.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="pillars">
                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-header">
                            <span class="pillar-num">01</span>
                            <h2>Read the code.</h2>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            hyprwhspr is fully open source under the MIT
                            license. Every line that touches your microphone,
                            audio, and keystrokes is public and auditable —
                            nothing compiled, obfuscated, or hidden away.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Want to verify exactly what happens to your audio,
                            from hotkey to text? You can.
                        </p>
                        <a
                            class="pillar-link"
                            href="https://github.com/goodroot/hyprwhspr"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener">Browse the source on GitHub ↗</a
                        >
                    </div>

                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-header">
                            <span class="pillar-num">02</span>
                            <h2>No company. No incentives.</h2>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            hyprwhspr is built and maintained by a <a
                                href="https://goodroot.ca">single developer</a
                            >. There's no company behind it, no investors, and no
                            business model that depends on your data.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            It exists because it's useful and building it was
                            interesting. Nobody stands to gain from your data, so
                            nobody ever will.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-header">
                            <span class="pillar-num">03</span>
                            <h2>Local means local.</h2>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            With a local backend — Parakeet, Whisper, onnx-asr,
                            Cohere Transcribe — your audio is processed entirely
                            on your own hardware. It is never sent to a server,
                            never stored unless you ask it to be, and never
                            leaves your machine.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            There's no telemetry, analytics, or crash reporting,
                            and during normal operation it makes no network calls
                            at all. The service is a local systemd process with
                            no reason to phone home and nowhere to phone home to.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="cloud-note">
                    <h3>A note on cloud backends</h3>
                    <p>
                        hyprwhspr optionally supports cloud transcription APIs —
                        Google Gemini, OpenAI, Groq, Cohere, ElevenLabs, and any
                        OpenAI-compatible endpoint. With a cloud backend, your
                        audio is sent to that provider's servers and subject to
                        their privacy policies.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        These are strictly opt-in: the default installation uses
                        local models only, and a cloud backend won't work until
                        you configure an API key yourself. It's a deliberate
                        choice you make — not something you're silently enrolled
                        in.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </main>

            <footer class="footer">
                <a href="/">hyprwhspr</a>
                <span class="sep">·</span>
                <a href="https://github.com/goodroot/hyprwhspr">GitHub</a>
                <span class="sep">·</span>
                <a
                    href="https://github.com/goodroot/hyprwhspr/blob/main/LICENSE"
                    >MIT License</a
                >
            </footer>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>

<style>
    .page {
        max-width: 680px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    /* Header */
    .header {
        padding: 1.5rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .back {
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        color: var(--comment);
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        transition: color 0.15s;
    }

    .back:hover {
        color: var(--blue);
    }

    /* Title block */
    main {
        padding: 3.5rem 0 4rem;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 3rem;
    }

    .title-block {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .page-tag {
        font-size: 0.68rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--green);
        border: 1px solid var(--green);
        border-radius: 3px;
        padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
        display: inline-block;
        width: fit-content;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 2.6rem);
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--fg-bright);
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        line-height: 1.15;
    }

    .lede {
        font-size: 1rem;
        color: var(--fg-dim);
        line-height: 1.7;
        max-width: 52ch;
    }

    /* Pillars */
    .pillars {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .pillar {
        padding: 2rem;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.85rem;
    }

    .pillar + .pillar {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .pillar:nth-child(odd) {
        background: var(--surface);
    }

    .pillar:nth-child(even) {
        background: var(--bg);
    }

    .pillar-header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: baseline;
        gap: 0.9rem;
    }

    .pillar-num {
        font-size: 0.68rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--comment);
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    .pillar h2 {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--fg-bright);
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }

    .pillar p {
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        color: var(--fg-dim);
        line-height: 1.75;
    }

    .pillar-link {
        font-size: 0.76rem;
        color: var(--blue);
        letter-spacing: 0.03em;
        margin-top: 0.25rem;
        transition: color 0.15s;
    }

    .pillar-link:hover {
        color: var(--cyan);
    }

    /* Cloud note */
    .cloud-note {
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: var(--bg);
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .cloud-note h3 {
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--fg-dim);
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .cloud-note p {
        font-size: 0.84rem;
        color: var(--fg-dim);
        line-height: 1.7;
    }

    /* Closing */
    .closing {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding-top: 2rem;
    }

    .closing p {
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        color: var(--comment);
        line-height: 1.75;
        font-style: italic;
    }

    /* Footer */
    .footer {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding: 1.5rem 0;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--comment);
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.6rem;
        align-items: center;
    }

    .sep {
        color: var(--border);
    }
</style>
